<h1>Template Help</h1>

<section class="dash-content-section">
	<h2>What is a Template?</h2>
	<p>
	Templates are Twig files that define how content is displayed on your website. They control the layout,
	structure, and presentation of your objects and collections.
	</p>

	<h2>Whitelabel Templates</h2>
	<p>
	Total CMS looks for several special built-in templates for common use cases. These templates must have
	a specific naming convention and be placed in the correct directory structure. For example: `whitelabel/login-above`.
	See the <a href="docs/whitelabel">whitelabel documentation</a> for a full list of built-in templates and their purposes.
	</p>

	<h2>Custom Templates</h2>
	<p>
	These are templates you have created. You can modify or delete them. Templates can be organized into
	folders for better management. You can add new templates by clicking the
	"<a href="templates/new">+ New Template</a>" button at the bottom of the page.
	</p>

	<h2>Template Organization</h2>
	<p>
	Use folders to organize your templates by purpose or section. For example, you might have folders like
	"grids", "pages", or "components". Folders are created automatically when you specify a folder path
	when saving a template.
	</p>
</section>
